page.title: 19MAGPIE GEESE IN REDDITCH
page.content: The{Magpie Goose}(Anseranas semipalmata) is a fascinating bird because nobody is quite sure whether it is a swan,a goose,a duck or if it is another family of birds all on its own. {Magpie Geese}are common in Australia. They are rare in Britain.However,there are some at Callow Hill Village, on a small pond along with some other water-fowl.Its feet are only partly webbed so it does not fit precisely into any group of water-fowl.It has a large knob on the forehead and abnormally long legs.Its plumage is black and white,black on the head, neck,wings and tail,and white on the rest of the body.Its beak is red and black,and its black feathers shine green and blue like a Magpie's,which is probably why it is called a {Magpie {Goose.}
